 to leave the car to get a discount 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[R4] The system must know the availability of power plugs at each station
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[R5] The system must be able to suggest the user the final station in order
 to ensure a uniform distribution of cars in the city 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
[G9] Users should know where the power grid stations are 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
[R1] User must be already logged or inside the car 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[R2] The system must be able to show the user where the power grid station
 are and if there are available power plugs
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
[G10] Users can report if the reserved car has damage 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
[R1] User must be already logged 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[R2] User must be able to report the damage of the car 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[R3] The system must take care of the damage car and notify it to an available
 maintenance operator 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[R4] As soon as the system receives the damage notify, it must let disappear
 the car from the list of the availables ones 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[R5] The system must delete the reservation of the car by the user that
 notify the damage 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
[G11] Allows users to cancel a reservation 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
[R1] User must be already logged 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[R2] User must already done a reservation for a car 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[R3] User must be able to cancel the reservation 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[R4] The system must be able to reinsert the car in the list of the availables
 ones 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[R5] User must cancel reservation within one hour from the reservation
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
[G12] Allows users to have discount 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
[R1] User must be already registered 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[R2] The system apply a discount of 10% when sensors on seats of the car
 pick up that there are more than two other passengers 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[R3] The system apply a discount of 20% when the car is left with no more
 of 50% of the battery empty 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[R4] The system apply a discount of 30% when the car is left at special
 parking areas and the user takes care of plugging the car into the power
 grid 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[R5] The system must know if a car is plugged into the power grid 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[R6] The system must know the percentage of battery of each car 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
[G13] Allows users to end the ride 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
[R1] User must be already registered 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[R2] User can end the ride if and only if the car is inside the safe area,
 otherwise he/she cannot lock the car 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[R3] As soon as the user end the ride and lock the car, the system reinsert
 the car in the list of available car 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[R4] When the ride is correctly end, the system stop to charge the user
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Operator
